<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Her movie I Care A Lot was recently acquired by Netflix.</p>

<p>And on Monday, Eiza Gonzalez posted a cute selfie to her Instagram Story in which she posed in a pretty sundress.</p>

<p>The Mexican actress, 30, gazes directly into the camera as she sits cross-legged on a wooden garden chair in the outdoor snap.</p>

<p>Flawless: Mexican actress Eiza Gonzalez, 30, posted a cute selfie to her Instagram Story in which she posed in a pretty sundress flashing a little cleavage in an outdoor shot</p>

<p>Eiza flashes a little cleavage in the floral print dress with spaghetti straps and gathered neckline.</p>

<p>The short frock's hem falls mid-thigh and she wears her shoulder-length brunette hair tucked behind one ear.</p>

<p>She accessorizes with three gold necklaces and is made up with black eye-liner and mascara along with some rosy lip color.</p>

<p>In the thriller I Care A Lot, which screened at the Toronto International Film Festival, Eiza stars with Rosamund Pike, Dianne Wiest, Peter Dinklage and Chris Messina.</p>

<p>Pike plays a woman who sets herself up as the legal guardian of elderly people who don't have anyone to take care of them. And it all goes swimmingly until she takes on the wrong elderly client.</p>

<p>Excited: A few days ago, the actress celebrated the news that Netflix had bought her latest movie I Care A Lot following its screening at the Toronto International Film Festival</p>

<p>Rising star: Eiza, who started out in telenovelas and worked with Vin Diesel in this year's Bloodshot, has also completed production on the yet-to-be-released Godzilla vs. Kong</p>

<p>Eiza started out in telenovelas and crossed over into Hollywood after being cast by Robert Rodriguez in the TV series From Dusk Till Dawn based on his vampire movies.</p>

<p>In 2017, she starred with Ansel Elgort in the movie Baby Driver and in 2018, with Steve Carell in the Robert Zemeckis film Welcome To Marwen.</p>

<p>She worked with Vin Diesel in the back-to-back movies Fast &amp; Furious Presents: Hobbs &amp; Shaw and Bloodshot and completed production on the yet-to-be-released Godzilla vs. Kong with Millie Bobbie Brown and Alexander Skarsgard.</p>

